.\" termin.al-name: changelog
.\" termin.al-usage: changelog
.\" termin.al-summary: Open changelog content.
.TH CHANGELOG 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
changelog \- Open changelog content.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
changelog
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the fixed virtual document
.B ~/changelog.md
as rendered Markdown in the current pane's inline viewer.
.SH VIEWER
Use j/k or arrows to move, PageUp/b and PageDown/Space to page, g/G to jump, / to search, n/N to move between matches, and q or Escape to return to the same shell. Mobile controls provide Escape, movement and Prefix.
.SH FAILURES
Extra arguments are rejected. Missing content produces the stable content-unavailable diagnostic; cancellation opens nothing.
.SH NOTES
The changelog is a read-only published document. Returning preserves the pane's transcript, history and working directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ changelog
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
now(1), about(1), open(1)
